    "A significant ~1 kbp deletion in the MPXV genome, notably in the OPG032 gene, has been found in Kamituga epidemic genome sequences (Vakaniaki et al., 2024).",
    "Deleting this gene also prevents the US CDC's Clade I-specific real-time PCR from detecting the virus (Li et al., 2010).",
